widgets_values:
IF YOU ARE NOT GETTING MY LEVEL OF DETAIL OR VERY NOISY IMAGES WITH BAD JPG COMPRESSION ARTIFACTS:

It probably means your Flowmatch isn't working. You MAY get this error log: 

The config attributes {'stochastic_sampling': False} were passed to FlowMatchEulerDiscreteScheduler, but are not expected and will be ignored. Please verify your scheduler_config.json configuration file.

(I had to downgrade to ComfyUI 0.3.77 to work)

nodes.title: WELCOME LETTER
widgets_values:
Luneva's Infinite Details Z Image Workflow!

This workflow was about 5 months and lots of hardwork in the making, since the research into Qwen realism techniques and now ZIT. 
If you incorporate this into your own public workflow, would appreciate the mention thanks!

All settings are very carefully calibrated to work together to achieve perfect short and long range details at max speed. 

Note: If image has blotchy Z Image noise, it is because your ComfyUI version broke Discrete Euler scheduler internally 
(as of posting this workflow) and you will need to downgrade to v0.3.77
